/*
 GOLDEN RULE
agar function baad me (future me) run hoga → closure (capture) hoga 
agar function turant run hoga → latest value milegi ✅


 STEP-BY-STEP CHECK

Step 1: ye dekh — function kab run ho raha hai?

👉 Case A: Turant run
function test() {
  console.log(x);
}
test();

✔️ latest value
❌ closure issue nahi


👉 Case B: Delay / future / event
setTimeout(() => {
  console.log(x);
}, 1000);

 closure (capture)


⚠️ MOST IMPORTANT SIGNALS

agar code me ye dikhe:
- setTimeout
- setInterval
- socket.on
- addEventListener
- Promise.then
- async/await callback

⚠️ ye closure trap hai


 Step 2: function return ho raha hai kya?

function outer() {
  let x = 10;

  return function inner() {
    console.log(x);
  };
}

- closure
kyunki inner future me run hoga


- Step 3: function kisi aur ko diya gaya hai?

button.addEventListener("click", () => {
  console.log(x);
});

- closure
kyunki browser baad me call karega


- IMPORTANT CLARIFICATION

closure sirf outer + inner function se nahi hota ❌

closure tab hota hai jab:
function apne scope ke bahar bhi survive kare ✅


- Examples

- Closure
useEffect(() => {
  socket.on("event", () => {
    console.log(receiverInfo);
  });
}, []);

kyunki socket future me call karega


✅ No closure problem
console.log(receiverInfo);

turant run → latest


- SUPER SIMPLE TRICK

apne aap se puch:
"ye function abhi run ho raha hai ya baad me?"

👉 agar:
abhi → latest value ✅
baad me → captured value 


- VISUAL MEMORY TRICK

Immediate call → live camera 
Delayed call → screenshot 


- FINAL SUMMARY

closure sirf nested function nahi ❌
closure = future execution + captured scope ✅


- FINAL LINE

Function agar "wait" karega → closure banega
Function agar "run now" hai → latest milega
*/
